column5: Well they did in game five,1963. I just watched a great classic April 04th 63. A year and 13 days, before I was born.  Boy could that Shack fly.  Stars of the game  Dave Keon Johhny Bower Dick Duff  I would say the boys in Montreal are a bit worried now.
Well if the leafs can stay out of the penalty box which they have been as of late, then they should have no problem tonight.
To bad you missed the game it was a goood one.watched it with my friend who was a habs fan  vance
Wasn't that around the last time they won the cup  Losers Even After Forty Seasons
Clash of the Titans tonite.  Hard Hitting, Fighting, End to end action, few penalties only Majors.  Great Canadian Hockey.  Flashbacks.
Ya I was 2 when the leafs last one the Cup.  I was at the Stanley Cup Parade in 1993 before the Habs fans thrashed the city of Montreal.  Its always a close game between these 2 teams.
Yeah...you had me goin' there fer a minute.

Ya, the Habs and Leafs games are close games. Yesterday, the Leafs at the end of the game had to score only 4 more goals to win the game. I am calling it a close game -  Now muskymatt, do not say "Losers Even After Forty Seasons". We must be nice to the Leafs. Let us say that the Leafs have been "re-building" since 1967 (their last Stanley Cup). It really gets interesting when the front office has also been re-building during most of this period of time.  But muskiematt, you are correct - they are losers. When a team is a loser 40 years ago, losers today and losers for 38 years in between, one can hontstly say - LOSERS  carp-starter
